 still [1, 2, 3], Do not add another elements as size is 4\nstk.increment(5, 100);                // stack becomes [101, 102, 103]\nstk.increment(2, 100);                // stack becomes [201, 202, 103]\nstk.pop();                            // return 103 --> Return top of the stack 103, stack becomes [201, 202]\nstk.pop();                            // return 202 --> Return top of the stack 202, stack becomes [201]\nstk.pop();                            // return 201 --> Return top of the stack 201, stack becomes []\nstk.pop();                            // return -1 --> Stack is empty return -1.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= maxSize, x, k <= 1000`\n\n- `0 <= val <= 100`\n\n- At most `1000` calls will be made to each method of `increment`, `push` and `pop` each separately.","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/design-a-stack-with-increment-operation/","problemName":"Design a Stack With Increment Operation","problemNumber":1381,"problemSlug":"design-a-stack-with-increment-operation","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":1381,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[{"assetIndex":0,"bytes":27105,"contentType":"image/jpeg","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1382-balance-a-binary-search-tree/1382-balance1-tree.jpg","originalUrl":"../../../images/1382-balance1-tree.jpg","sha256":"1a0f92c1081eb20f9674fe8091d9d0238d0b10a71166748725cb9385f608420e"},{"assetIndex":1,"bytes":6436,"contentType":"image/jpeg","localPath":"leetcode_seed/assets/problems/1382-balance-a-binary-search-tree/1382-balanced2-tree.jpg","originalUrl":"../../../images/1382-balanced2-tree.jpg","sha256":"02fef83d689a908310666926e23a7c4af6ea746cda280c436ac59fe4ad5133d6"}],"categories":["Divide and Conquer","Greedy","Tree","Depth-First Search","Binary Search Tree","Binary Tree"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"Given the `root` of a binary search tree, return *a **balanced** binary search tree with the same node values*. If there is more than one answer, return **any of them*