ximum performance of the team. That is, performance = (2 + 10 + 5) * min(5, 4, 7) = 68.\n\n**Example 3:**\n\nInput: n = 6, speed = [2,10,3,1,5,8], efficiency = [5,4,3,9,7,2], k = 4\nOutput: 72\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= k <= n <= 10⁵`\n\n- `speed.length == n`\n\n- `efficiency.length == n`\n\n- `1 <= speed[i] <= 10⁵`\n\n- `1 <= efficiency[i] <= 10⁸`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/maximum-performance-of-a-team/","problemName":"Maximum Performance of a Team","problemNumber":1383,"problemSlug":"maximum-performance-of-a-team","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":1383,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["Database"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"Table: `Product`","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"+---------------+---------+\n| Column Name   | Type    |\n+---------------+---------+\n| product_id    | int     |\n| product_name  | varchar |\n+---------------+---------+\nproduct_id is the primary key (column with unique values) for this table.\nproduct_name is the name of the product.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"Table: `Sales`","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"+---------------------+---------+\n| Column Name         | Type    |\n+---------------------+---------+\n| product_id          | int     |\n| period_start        | date    |\n| period_end          | date    |\n| average_daily_sales | int     |\n+---------------------+---------+\nproduct_id is the primary key (column with unique values) for this table. \nperiod_start and period_end indicate the start and end date for the sales period, and both dates are inclusive.\nThe average_daily_sales column holds the average daily sales amount of the items for the period.\nThe dates of the sales years are between 2018 to 2020.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"Write a solution to report the total sales amount of each item for each year, with corresponding `product_name`, `product_id`, `report_year`, and `total_amount`.\n\nReturn the result table **ordered** by `product_id` and `report_year`.\n\nThe result format is in the following example.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":5,"text":"Input: \nProduct table:\n+------------+--------------+\n| product_id | product_name |\n+------------+--------------+\n| 1          | LC Phone     |\n| 2          | LC T-Shirt   |\n| 3          | LC Keychain  |\n+------------+--------------+\nSales table:\n+------------+--------------+-------------+---------------------+\n| product_id | period_start | period_end  | average_daily_sales |\n+------------+--------------+-------------+---------------------+\n| 1          | 2019-01-25   | 2019-02-28  | 100                 |\n| 2          | 2018-12-01   | 2020-01-01  | 10                  |\n| 3          | 2019-12-01   | 2020-01-31  | 1                   |\n+------------+--------------+-------------+---------------------+\nOutput: \n+------------+--------------+-------------+--------------+\n| product_id | product_name | report_year | total_amount |\n+------------+--------------+-------------+--------------+\n| 1          | LC Phone     |    2019     | 3500         |\n| 2          | LC T-Shirt   |    2018     | 310          |\n| 2          | LC T-Shirt   |    2019     | 3650         |\n| 2          | LC T-Shirt   |    2020     | 10           |\n| 3          | LC Keychain  |    2019     | 31           |\n| 3          | LC Keychain  |    2020     | 31           |\n+------------+--------------+-------------+--------------+\nExplanation: \nLC Phone was sold for the period of 2019-01-25 to 2019-02-28, and there are 35 days for this period. Total amount 35*100 = 3500. \nLC T-shirt was sold for the period of 2018-12-01 to 2020-01-01, and there are 31, 365, 1 days for years 2018, 2019 and 2020 respectively.\nLC Keychain was sold for the period of 2019-12-01 to 2020-01-31, and there are 31, 31 days for years 2019 and 2020 respectively.","type":"code"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Database"],"cre